    rookRuns: `proposals lead with the buyer's outcome`,
    shortAnswer: `Structure a sales proposal to lead with the buyer's world, not yours: an executive summary of their problem and desired outcome, your understanding of their situation, the proposed solution tied to their goals, the value case and pricing, proof, and clear next steps. Buyer-centric proposals that open with the problem win more than company-centric ones that open with an About Us.`,
