    shortAnswer: `Plan a sales negotiation by setting your target and walk-away point, knowing your BATNA, anticipating the buyer's goals and pressures, and preparing your tradeables and give-gets in advance. Most negotiation outcomes are decided by preparation, not by improvisation on the call, so the plan is where you win or lose.`,
