    shortAnswer: `Handle "no budget" by recognizing that no allocated budget is different from no value or no ability to fund. If the pain is real and quantified, help the buyer build the business case that creates budget, explore timing around the next budget cycle, or find discretionary funds. Accepting the no at face value abandons deals that are genuinely fundable.`,
