    shortAnswer: `Commit a forecast by only including deals you are highly confident will close in the period, backed by evidence: a verbal commitment, a mapped path to signature, and an engaged economic buyer. A commit is a promise, not a hope, so under-committing and delivering builds more credibility than over-committing and missing. Protect your forecast credibility ruthlessly.`,
