    shortAnswer: `Build a sales battlecard by keeping it short and scannable, focusing on how to win against a specific competitor rather than an exhaustive feature comparison, arming reps with discovery questions that expose the competitor's weaknesses, and keeping it ruthlessly current. A battlecard reps can absorb in the moment beats a comprehensive document nobody reads.`,
